        <guid>http://localhost:61314/en/post/20240908/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="http://localhost:61314/post/20240908/media/22.jpg" alt="Featured image of post August" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let’s start with a bit of barking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;video-wrapper&#34;&gt;
    &lt;video
    controls
    src=&#34;464870852.mp4&#34;
    
    
    &gt;
        &lt;p&gt;
            Your browser doesn&#39;t support HTML5 video. Here is a
            &lt;a href=&#34;464870852.mp4&#34;&gt;link to the video&lt;/a&gt; instead.
        &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/video&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the past two months, my inner emotions have been shattered into pieces. These are some delicate emotions buried in my heart. Everyone said that I am very sunny and positive, but in fact it is just my disguise. I have fallen into severe self-doubt and self-inflicted internal friction. Therefore, I constantly use scientific research work and small and medium-sized activities in life to numb myself so that I will not be idle, because when I am idle, I will have random thoughts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore, some new skills were upgraded in the process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-the-town-looks-like&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#what-the-town-looks-like&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    What the town looks like
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Where I come from, the buildings are very low and the town is very peaceful. The sunset is the same every day, but every time I look at it I have a different feeling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;video-wrapper&#34;&gt;
